 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SONG VIII. Praise to GOD for learning to Read.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">THE Praises of my Tongue</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">I offer to the LORD,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That I was taught, and learnt so young</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To read his holy Word.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That I am brought to know</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The Danger I was in,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">By Nature and by Practice too,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">A wretched Slave to Sin.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That I am lead to see</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">I can do nothing well;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And whither shall a Sinner flee</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To save himself from Hell?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Dear LORD. this Book of thine</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Informs me where to go,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For Grace to pardon all my Sin,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And make me holy too.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Here I can read, and learn</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How CHRIST, the Son of GOD,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Has undertook our great Concern;</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Our Ransom cost his Blood.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And now he reigns above,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">He sends his Spirit down</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To shew the Wonders of his Love,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And make his Gospel known.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">O may that Spirit teach,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And make my Heart receive</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Those Truths which all thy Servants preach</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And all thy Saints believe.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Then shall I praise the LORD</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In a more chearful Strain,</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That I was taught to read his Word,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And have not learnt in vain.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
